<h1>Christopher Smith</h1>
<h2>Online Profile of Christopher Smith</h2>
<P>I work with employed professionals 
    who do not have to make a move but would at least like the opportunity 
    to hear about what's out there in the event that their dream job surfaces. 
    I invest my time with people I feel have marketable skills and future potential, 
    learn what they do, where they are and where they want to take their career and
    try to get them there a little faster!</P>

    <p>Experienced in staffing, recruitment process outsourcing, and direct
        hire/headhunting.</p>

</body>
<p>Experience

    Publicis Sapient - Manager Talent Acquisition
    April 2022 - Present (1 year 1 month)
    Boston, Massachusetts, United States

    Publicis Sapient is a digital transformation partner helping established
    organizations get to their future, digitally-enabled state, both in the way they
    work and the way they serve their customers.
    We help unlock value through a start-up mindset and modern methods, fusing
    strategy, consulting and customer experience with agile engineering and
    problem-solving creativity.
    
    Huge - Senior Recruiter
    October 2021 - April 2022 (7 months)
    Brooklyn, New York, United States
    MAKE HUGE MOVES.

    Huge is a global experience agency made up of creatives, designers,
    technologists, strategists, and data scientists. We help companies elevate the
    human experience by creating unified brand experiences that people love. We
    work with clients such as Google, McDonalds, FCA, Brooks Running, P&G,
    and others, who are as committed to shaping culture and defining the future
    as we are. Headquartered in Brooklyn, we currently have more than 1,200
    employees working across 13 offices in North America, Latin America, Europe,
    and Asia.
    
    Toledo Tool and Die - Human Resources Executive / Corporate Recruiter
    September 2019 - October 2021 (2 years 2 months)
    Toledo, Ohio Area

    We Offer a Wide Range of Services: Since we strive to perform every task
    our clients might require from a tool and die company, we figured we would need
    a lot of space. That is why Toledo Tool and Die is housed in a 105,000 square
    foot facility. We do everything from tool designing and in-house builds to highvolume 
    mass production of stamping assemblies and other machines.
    
    endevis Recruiting | Retention - Professional Recruiter
    May 2015 - September 2019 (4 years 5 months)
    Toledo, Ohio Area

    endevis is in the business of talent engagement. . .
    We successfully motivate and engage talent on all levels, driving organizations
    in the planning, selecting and developing of great talent through our 3 distinct
    business solutions.
    • Recruitment Process Outsourcing
    • Professional Technical Staffing
    • Professional Direct Placement
    endevis understands that each client we serve is different, and each
    opportunity or project we undertake is unique. Our client's investment into
    each project differs as well. We will not take a "standard" approach to our
    delivery. We believe our consultative approach is what our clients value in
    working with endevis. We are able to be creative and flexible within our talent
    acquisition solutions and ensure we deliver the most comprehensive and
    effective services.
    
    Pontoon Solutions - Talent Acquisitions Consultant - Multiple Accounts
    July 2013 - October 2014 (1 year 4 months)
    Toledo, Ohio Area

    Experience in managing the full life-cycle recruiting process including sourcing,
    interviewing, presenting candidates, and negotiating offers. Work daily to
    develop and maintain strong business relationships with internal clients by
    developing and executing recruiting strategies designed to identify qualified
    candidates through various recruiting tools. Responsible for capturing data
    in Applicant Tracking System and generating of reports. During this time I
    worked actively for 12+ clients in our RPO division.
    Experience sourcing and screening candidates
    Experience navigating and sourcing through social media channels
    Experience prioritizing and managing a variety of tasks
    Internet savvy and experienced in mining online databases
    Ability to analyze and interpret metrics to drive performance.
    Proficient with Microsoft Office Suite of applications.
    Ability to build trust, develop and maintain relationships with all stakeholders.
    Ability to multi-task in a fast paced, ever changing environment.
    Strong written and verbal communication skills and presentation skills.
    Proven track record of exceeding monthly goals
       
    Ohio Teaching Family Association - Alternate Teaching / Foster Parent - Youth 12 - 20
    May 2010 - July 2013 (3 years 3 months)
    Sylvania, OH
    Promote, assist, and support the development of treatment programs for
